bug.short_desc: terminator shows duplicated key in in group terminals
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1187317 captured terminator terminal
Description of problem:
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Fedora24
$ dnf info terminator Thu 04 Aug 2016 11:41:37 AM KST Last metadata expiration check: 0:00:13 ago on Thu Aug 4 11:41:34 2016. Installed Packages Name : terminator Arch : noarch Epoch : 0 Version : 0.98 Release : 3.fc24 Size : 11 M Repo : @System From repo : @commandline Summary : Store and run multiple GNOME terminals in one window URL : http://gnometerminator.blogspot.com/p/introduction.html License : GPLv2 Description : Multiple GNOME terminals in one window. This is a project to produce : an efficient way of filling a large area of screen space with : terminals. This is done by splitting the window into a resizeable : grid of terminals. As such, you can produce a very flexible : arrangements of terminals for different tasks.
How reproducible:
launch terminator and split windows as two. Super+G and input character, then you can see duplicated character in other windows. only active windows showed normal key strokes.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. launch terminator 2. split windows 2 or more 3. super+G and stroke keys
Actual results:
duplicated key storkes in non active windows
Expected results:
same key strokes as active windows
Additional info:
below link is same issue in terminator launchpad. https://bugs.launchpad.net/terminator/+bug/1318542
